-- `Keccak.*` and `MlKemDecaps.*` resolve through the enclosing `Dregg2.Crypto` namespace.
open Dregg2.Crypto.AcvpHex (hexBytes hexOfLen)

/-! ## The CAVP vectors.

Each block is: a docstring naming the CAVP file, the vector id and the branch it exercises; the
`native_decide` KAT itself; and a `#guard` that the pinned hex is well-formed and has exactly the
CAVP-declared byte length, so a truncated transcription fails at elaboration rather than silently
becoming a shorter byte string. -/

/-- CAVP `SHAKE128ShortMsg.rsp`, `Len = 0` -- empty message; re-anchors `Keccak.shake128_empty_kat` (first 16 bytes).

Message 0 B, output 16 B. -/
